<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-009-261 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 500 704</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Nov 19 1991 v5 n40 p12(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Smart stacks drive multimedia apps; Entrypaq uses AI forinteractivity. (Albathion Software Inc.'s Entrypaq Professional3.0 program development software)(artificial intelligence)(Product Announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ratcliffe, Mitch.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Albathion Software Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Entrypaq Professional 3.0 (Program development software) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Program Development SoftwareMultimedia SoftwareProduct IntroductionArtificial IntelligenceExpert SystemsInteractive Video.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Entrypaq uses AI for interactivityandM;By Mitch RatcliffeandM;San Francisco -- Interactivity can bring a multimedia presentation to life,but adding interactive capabilities that allow presentations to reason aboutspecific questions has required costly artificial-intelligence software -- upuntil now.andM;Albathion Software Inc. wants to change that with an expert-system package,Entrypaq Professional 3.0, that lets users write logical rules to controlapplications and documents for use in presentations or training.andM;Available now for $149, the System 7-compatible application is based onHyperTalk and provides a HyperCard front end for building and debuggingknowledge bases.andP;  Its rule-based inference engine helps users build&quot;intelligent multimedia,&quot; Albathion said.andM;For example, an Entrypaq stack could help diagnose an automobile engineproblem.andP;  Since Entrypaq can link MacroMind-Paracomp Inc.'s Director moviesto specific objects on screen or to typed viewer input, it could play briefanimated sequences to show what engine parts need checking.andP;  It might alsorecommend needed repairs.andM;Programming is relatively simple: Users type and edit rules in a series ofwindows.andP;  By creating &quot;if/then&quot; statements, users can program an Entrypaqstack to launch applications or open documents.andM;Entrypaq can assemble the elements of an individual &quot;case&quot; -- enginetemperature, spark-plug type and months since last tuneup, in theengine-problem example -- into &quot;frames,&quot; or objects that represent all theelements.andP;  Once framed, cases can be connected to one another in a graphicalenvironment.andM;Since Entrypaq supports both plain English &quot;if/then&quot; statements andobject-based logical programming, it is comparable to artificial-intelligenceapplications that sell for $5,000 or more, Albathion said.andM;An IBM PC version of Entrypaq, based on Spinnaker Corp.'s PLUS,  will shipnext month.andP;  Knowledge bases created in the Mac version can be converted torun on the PC.andM;Albathion Software Inc. is at 4372 24th St., San Francisco, Calif.andP;  94114.andO;Phone (415) 824-2737; fax (415) 821-6103.andO;</TEXT></DOC>